  "response": "Most scholars believe that Jesus was likely born sometime between **March and September**.\n\nHere's why:\n\n*   **Shepherds in the Fields:** The Gospel of Luke mentions shepherds tending their flocks in the fields at night. This would have been unlikely in the colder months of December and January in Judea.\n*   **Tax Census:** The Romans usually conducted tax censuses after the harvest season, which would have been in the fall. This could explain why Joseph and Mary were traveling to Bethlehem.\n\nWhile a specific month cannot be pinpointed, the arguments above strongly suggest that a spring to early fall timeframe is more plausible than December.\n\nIt's important to remember that the December 25th date was chosen by the Church centuries later and is not based on direct biblical evidence.",
